Privacy Policy for Mind Flip

Effective Date: January 14, 2026

1. Introduction This Privacy Policy applies to the Mind Flip app (hereby referred to as "Application") created by [Your Name or Company Name] (hereby referred to as "Service Provider") as an Ad-Supported service. This service is intended for use "AS IS".

2. Information Collection and Use The Application collects information when you download and use it. This information may include:

    Device Information: Your device's Internet Protocol address (e.g. IP address), operating system version, and configuration of the app.

    Usage Data: Information regarding how you use the Application, such as the duration of game sessions and your in-game progress.

The Service Provider may use the information provided to contact you from time to time to provide you with important information, required notices, and marketing promotions.

3. Third-Party Access (AdMob) Only aggregated, anonymized data is periodically transmitted to external services to aid the Service Provider in improving the Application and their service. The Service Provider may share your information with third parties in the ways that are described in this privacy statement.

This Application uses Google AdMob to display banner and rewarded ads. AdMob may collect and use identifiers on your device (such as the Advertising ID) to serve personalized ads based on your interests and to analyze ad performance.

    Please note that the Service Provider creates the Application but does not control the data collection practices of Google AdMob.

    Link to privacy policy of third-party service providers used by the Application:

        Google Play Services

        AdMob

4. Location Data The Service Provider does not explicitly request or track your precise location data. However, third-party ad networks (like AdMob) may use your IP address to determine your approximate location (City/Country level) to serve relevant advertisements.

5. Cookies The Service Provider does not explicitly use cookies. However, the Application may use third-party code and libraries that use "cookies" to collect information and improve their services. You have the option to either accept or refuse these cookies and know when a cookie is being sent to your device.

6. Security The Service Provider is concerned about safeguarding the confidentiality of your information. The Service Provider provides physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect information the Service Provider processes and maintains.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. The Service Provider will notify you of any changes to the Privacy Policy by updating this page with the new Privacy Policy. You are advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes, as continued use is deemed approval of all changes.

8. Contact Us If you have any questions regarding privacy while using the Application, or have questions about the practices, please contact the Service Provider via email at: [Your Email Address Here]
